Teams of cleaners, known as 'Lonely Death Squads', clear houses where elderly people lay dead for  months . 
 Police remove decomposing corpses but the clean-up crews are faced with houses filled with rubbish and flies . 
 In rapidly ageing Japan, more and more people are dying alone and unnoticed in a country of 127 million people . 
 One in four people in Japan is over 65 - with increasingly loose family bonds adding to the isolation of the elderly . 
 